<TITLE> Bomb kills four NATO soldiers in Afghanistan </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 KABUL, Sun Mar 15,(bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Four NATO-led soldiers were killed by a roadside bomb in Afghanistan on Sunday, the alliance said, one of the deadliest attacks against foreign troops in recent weeks in the country. Violence has increased since last year in Afghanistan where the Taliban, ousted in a US-led invasion in 2001, have made a comeback in their campaign to drive out foreign troops. The latest deaths happened in the east of the country, NATO said in a statement, without identifying the nationality of the victims. Most foreign troops deployed in the east are Americans. On Saturday, two NATO soldiers, one in the east and one in the south, were killed in two separate attacks by the insurgents, the alliance said earlier. Some 70,000 foreign troops under NATO and the US military are struggling to defeat the resurgent al Qaeda-backed Taliban and the United States plans to send 17,000 extra troops this year to stabilize Afghanistan. US-led troops invaded Afghanistan and overthrew the Taliban government after it refused to hand over al Qaeda leaders wanted by Washington for the September 11 attacks on the United St
